abstract: Additional particulars of the loss of the Arctic were received in this City yesterday. The latest intelligence is confirmatory of the leading facts already published, but we have the satisfaction of being able to announce that the loss of life is considerably less than was at first reported. Doubts still exist, however, in regard to the great majority of the Arctic's passengers; the fate of three boats being as yet wholly unknown.
